christopher j h wright  wikipedia christopher j h wright from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search christopher jh wright revd dr christopher j h wright born  is an anglican clergyman and an old testament scholar he is currently the international ministries director of langham partnership international he was the principal of all nations christian college he is an honorary member of all souls church langham place in london uk contents  life  childhood and education  early professional experience  foreign mission service  all nations christian college  current role  personal life  writing  references  external links lifeedit childhood and educationedit wright was born in belfast northern ireland in  his parents were missionaries in brazil though chris as the youngest son was born after they came back at the end of the second world war he grew up in belfast and was nurtured as an irish presbyterian he studied classics at cambridge in the s and then started his career as a highschool teacher in grosvenor high school belfast in the s he studied for his phd at cambridge university in cambridge england in the field of theology specialising in old testament economic ethics his book from this work was published as gods people in gods land eerdmans and paternoster early professional experienceedit wright was ordained in the anglican church of england in  and served as an assistant pastor in the parish church of st peter  st paul tonbridge kent england foreign mission serviceedit in  wright moved to india with his wife liz and four children to teach at union biblical seminary ubs in pune for five years at this time he and liz were mission partners with crosslinks an evangelical anglican mission agency while at ubs he taught a variety of old testament courses at bd and mth levels all nations christian collegeedit in  wright returned to the uk as academic dean at all nations christian college an international training centre for crosscultural mission he was appointed principal there in september  and held that post for eight years current roleedit in september  wright was appointed to his present role as the international ministries director of the langham partnership international lpi wright and his wife belong to all souls church langham place where he enjoys preaching from time to time as a member of the ministry team this is also the church of course where lpis founder john stott was rector emeritus personal lifeedit wright enjoys running birding and watching rugby football he has a passion to bring to life the relevance of the old testament to christian mission and ethics he has written several books mostly on that area he loves preaching and teaching the bible which he does now mostly through the langham preaching seminars in different parts of the world when not travelling around the world for this ministry and giving international leadership to lpi chris gives about three months of each year to his continuing writing projects wright and his wife liz live in london and have four adult children and a growing number of grandchildren writingedit users guide to the bible lion manuals chariot victor  gods people in gods land family land and property in the old testament grand rapids eerdmans exeter uk paternoster  knowing jesus through the old testament harpercollins  walking in the ways of the lord the ethical authority of the old testament intervarsity press  deuteronomy new international biblical commentaryhendrickson  the uniqueness of jesus thinking clearly series mill hill london and grand rapids monarch reprint  available in the united states through kregel publications po box  grand rapids mi   the message of ezekiel the bible speaks today intervarsity press  old testament ethics for the people of god leicester england and downers grove ill intervarsity press revised updated and expanded version of living as the people of god and an eye for an eye  the mission of god unlocking the bibles grand narrativeivp academic  life through god’s word psalm  milton keynes authentic and keswick ministries  knowing the holy spirit through the old testament oxford monarch press downers grove ivp  knowing god the father through the old testament ivp academic  salvation belongs to our god celebrating the bible’s central story global christian library nottingham ivp christian doctrine in global perspective downers grove ivp  the god i don’t understand reflections on tough questions of faith grand rapids zondervan  mission of god’s people the biblical theology for life grand rapids zondervan  sweeter than honey langham preaching resources  becoming like jesus langham preaching resources  let the gospels preach the gospel langham preaching resources  referencesedit  a b leadership langham partnership langham partnership retrieved  may    a b all souls langham place staff and leadership all souls langham place retrieved  may    a b c profile christopher jh wright retrieved  may    john stott biography local influence langham partnership retrieved  may   external linksedit langham partnership international all souls church authority control worldcat identities viaf  isni     sudoc x bnf cb data retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlechristopherjhwrightoldid categories christian writersold testament scholarsthcentury church of england clergyamerican christiansenglish anglican theologians birthsliving peopleeuropean university and college presidentspeople from belfastanglican biblical scholarsbritish biblical scholarshidden categories engvarb from june use dmy dates from june articles which use infobox templates with no data rowsarticles with hcardswikipedia articles with viaf identifierswikipedia articles with isni identifierswikipedia articles with bnf identifiers navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom a