ustice society and culture and individual morality this fresh illuminating study provides a clear basis for a biblical ethic that is faithful to the god of both testaments a theological social and economic framework for exploring old testament ethicsprovides the basis for an ethic faithful to both old and new testamentsthoroughly revisedexpanded with  more pages updated to include more consideration of contemporary issues ecology poverty hermeneutics product information▼▲ format pdf downloadvendor ivp academicpublication date isbn isbn  other customers also purchased ebook more info add to wishlist signposts to god how modern physics and astronomy point the way to belief  ebook peter bussey peter bussey ivp academic    epub  retail  save   ebook more info add to wishlist questioning your doubts a harvard phd explores challenges to faith  ebook christina powell christina powell intervarsity press    epub  retail  save   ebook more info add to wishlist do we need the new testament letting the old testament speak for itself  ebook john e goldingay john e goldingay ivp academic    epub  retail  save    stars out of   reviews ebook more info add to wishlist the acts of the apostles interpretation history and theology  ebook osvaldo padilla osvaldo padilla ivp academic    epub  retail  save    stars out of   reviews related products ebook more info add to wishlist science creation and the bible reconciling rival theories of origins  ebook richard f carlson tremper longman iii richard f carlson tremper longman iii ivp academic    epub  retail  save   add to cart add to wishlist el dios pródigo the prodigal god dvd timothy keller timothy keller zondervan    dvd  retail  save   add to cart add to wishlist the way of the lord christian pilgrimage today nt wright nt wright wm b eerdmans publishing co    trade paperback  retail  save   add to cart add to wishlist biblia rva  letra grande imitacion piel negra con indice large print imitation leather black with index editorial mu